## 🚀 Feature Proposal

1. Either a method to unlock all the cells (and then to use the existing methods to lock particular rows)
OR 
2. Create an excel with all cells unlocked by default.

All this without increasing the size of excel by much.

## Motivation

Main motivation was to lock the headers for excel and then it being used as a template. But the problem raised when we create a new excel file, excel by default locks all the cells, And as of now there is no feature for unlocking all cells in the excel without adding some metadata and thus making the file large.

## Example

Current Unoptimised Implementation :- 
   worksheet1.protect('your_password', {
      selectLockedCells: true,
      selectUnlockedCells: true,
      formatCells: false,
      formatColumns: false,
      formatRows: false,
      insertColumns: false,
      insertRows: false,
      insertHyperlinks: false,
      deleteColumns: false,
      deleteRows: false,
      sort: false,
      autoFilter: false,
      pivotTables: false,
      objects: false,
      scenarios: false,
    });

    // Unlock cells that are not in the first 2 rows
    const maxRows = 10000; // Adjust this number based on your needs
    const maxCols = 17; // Adjust this number based on your needs (e.g., Q column is 17)
    for (let rowNumber = 2; rowNumber <= maxRows; rowNumber++) {
      for (let colNumber = 1; colNumber <= maxCols; colNumber++) {
        const cell = worksheet1.getCell(rowNumber, colNumber);
        cell.protection = { locked: false };
      }
    }
